This removes an unnecessary assertion that triggers in OPynSim's test suite
under debug mode.

The reason it's unnecessary is because OpenSim sockets can now work without
a connection (it just performs a slow tree traversal instead), but this assertion
slipped through because OpenSim is almost never built in debug mode by upstream.

---

diff --git a/OpenSim/Common/Component.h b/OpenSim/Common/Component.h
index 49addb93e..0f4840195 100644
--- a/OpenSim/Common/Component.h
+++ b/OpenSim/Common/Component.h
@@ -1033,7 +1033,6 @@ public:
     const T& getConnectee(const std::string& name) const {
         // get the Socket and check if it is connected.
         const Socket<T>& socket = getSocket<T>(name);
-        OPENSIM_ASSERT_FRMOBJ(socket.isConnected());
         return socket.getConnectee();
     }
 
